 Nation at a Glance
				 																Fire kills Indians				 																																																	Dubai, Nov. 18 (PTI): Six Indians were among 28 people killed in a gas pipeline fire in an oil-rich desert area of eastern Saudi Arabia today.				 																																																										Twenty-eight people, including five employees of Aramco, died, state oil conglomerate Aramco said. They said the identity of the deceased Indians could not be ascertained immediately. The fire did not disrupt gas supplies.				 																Amjad 				 																																																	 Kanpur (PTI): Ustad Amjad Ali Khan has questioned the relevance of reality music shows, saying such programmes cannot judge the worth of a candidate. The knowledge of classical music is imperative to earn a name and success in this field, the sarod maestro said on the sidelines of a cultural programme.				 																AIIMS fined				 																																																	New Delhi (PTI): A doctor who lost his speech after a botched operation at AIIMS six years ago has been awarded a compensation of Rs 1 lakh by the Delhi consumer commission. The commission held the institute guilty of gross medical negligence during the operation on J.S. Bedi.				 																Wolf attack				 																																																	Nasik (PTI): Six persons were injured when a wolf attacked them in Janori village here, police said on Sunday. The animal also attacked some cows in the village. The wolf was later stoned to death. 				 																Chemist held				 																																																	Moga (Punjab) (PTI): A chemist has been arrested in this district for allegedly carrying drugs and tablets to sell illegally, police said. A search of Ahmed Alis bag led to the seizure of 71,000 tablets, 4,600 capsules, 485 injections and 185 bottles of cough syrup. 				 																Accident				 																																																	 Madurai (PTI): Five persons, including four women, were killed and 26 injured when two government buses collided at Vadugapatti, 20km from here, on Sunday, police said. The injured were taken to the Madurai Government Rajaji Hospital.
